						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is damaged and incomplete. It records a gift of 62 cows for the daily supply of milk during the three services at 5 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> for each service, for the sacred bath of Mūlasthānattu-Mahādēva at Tiruviḍaimarudil by <hi rend="bold">Mōśi Orriyūraṉ Kūttaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Araiyaṉ Kūttaṉ.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">dēvakanmis</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tiraimūr, the <hi rend="italic">nagarattār</hi> of Tiruviḍaimarudil and the trustee Śiṟṟiṅgaṇ-uḍaiyāṉ (mentioned in No. 346 above) seem to have jointly accepted the gift. This is also probably an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
